result.execSummary:
The defendant Dominic D Williams-Lewis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order - Injunction [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Dominic D Williams-Lewis in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  Sarra Mae Kiaie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Courts finds that State has complied with victim notification.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  

Sentencing proceeded.   Statements made as to sentencing.   Court ordered defendant to serve 14 days in the House of Correction, with 14 days credit for time served.  TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

Court ordered applicable costs, fees and surcharges to be paid by July 28, 2016, or if not paid, a CIVIL JUDGMENT.  

Court advised defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.

48USC Section 922(g)(9) prohibits possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence.
